The paper introduces a new centrality measure in Network Science and describes scalable algorithms for computing it on large graphs. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Statistical Learning (cs.SD). However, given the focus on network analysis and centrality measures, cs.SI and cs.SD are the most likely sub-categories.
